FuncDef: The undo upgrade rollback command cancels the timeout period of the rollback timer for a system software upgrade. The undo upgrade rollback command cancels the timeout period of the rollback timer for a system software upgrade. By default, the rollback timer is not enabled.
ExtraInfo:
If the version rollback function is disabled, the system will not perform version rollback whether any users successfully log in to the device in a specified period of time.
By default, the version rollback function is disabled. After each version rollback completes, the version rollback function is disabled again.
